    <stitle>T 444E Diesel Engine Diagnostics (NAVPAK) (1997) - SECTION 3.5: ELECTRONIC CONTROL SYSTEM DIAGNOSTICS,
        ACCELERATOR PEDAL POSITION SENSOR/IVS SWITCH (APS/IVS) - BRAKE SWITCH CIRCUITS (BRAKE) - FAULT DETECTION
        MANAGEMENT
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="PROCTYPE" graphiccount="1">
        <title>FAULT DETECTION MANAGEMENT</title>
        <para>The ECM continuously monitors terminals 43 and 44 for voltage. Should there be a voltage at one of the
            terminals and not at the other, the ECM will set a fault code.
        </para>
        <para>When Flash code 222 is active, all features using brake signal inputs will be disabled.</para>
        <para>This code will not cause the Warn Engine Light to illuminate.</para>
        <para>Refer to
            <emph type="BOLD">Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1901717">3.24</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            for the barometric pressure sensor circuit diagram and
            <emph type="BOLD">Table
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1901718">3.5</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            for the voltage checks.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1901717" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="eg1219" filename="../figeg1/eg1219.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 3.24 Brake Switch Circuits (Brake) Circuit Diagram</caption>
